[{"id":"VH967115","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a conducting sphere with a charge of positive uppercase Q. Point B is located on the furthest left side of the sphere and Point A is located on the furthest right side of the sphere.\" height=\"165\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH967115.g03.png\" width=\"200\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A conducting sphere has a net charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . Points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are on opposite sides of the surface of the sphere, as shown. If a point charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"positive lowercase q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mtext>q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is moved from point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in a straight line through the center of the sphere, the work done to move the charge is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . If a point charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"positive lowercase q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mtext>q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is moved from point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> along the surface of the sphere, the work done is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S\"><math alttext=\"W sub S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S\"><math alttext=\"W sub S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and gives evidence to support this comparison?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH967115_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S is greater than W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub S is greater than W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mo>&gt;</mo><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the point charge is moved a greater distance for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S\"><math alttext=\"W sub S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S\"><math alttext=\"W sub S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S is less than W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub S is less than W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mo>&lt;</mo><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because no work is done only when the point charge moves along the surface.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S is less than W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub S is less than W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mo>&lt;</mo><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because there is more work done moving the charge to the center of the sphere and back to the surface than moving the charge along the surface.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S equals W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub S equals W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the displacement for each path is the same.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub S equals W sub C\"><math alttext=\"W sub S equals W sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow></msub><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because no work is done along either path, regardless of displacement.</p>"],"answer":4}]